{"id": "EUVD-2024-51779", "enisaUuid": "5c4a7e86-39aa-34d2-94aa-c31f3e117aa9", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nfs/proc/task_mmu: prevent integer overflow in pagemap_scan_get_args()\n\nThe \"arg->vec_len\" variable is a u64 that comes from the user at the start\nof the function.  The \"arg->vec_len * sizeof(struct page_region))\"\nmultiplication can lead to integer wrapping.  Use size_mul() to avoid\nthat.\n\nAlso the size_add/mul() functions work on unsigned long so for 32bit\nsystems we need to ensure that \"arg->vec_len\" fits in an unsigned long.", "datePublished": "2024-12-02T13:44:39", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-01T20:17:11", "baseScore": 5.5, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H", "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/adee03f8903c58a6a559f21388a430211fac8ce9", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/669b0cb81e4e4e78cff77a5b367c7f70c0c6c05e"], "aliases": ["CVE-2024-53107"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.04, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "08044c9b-9ce6-3c54-89f0-5a635b6ec8e5", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "52526ca7fdb905a768a93f8faa418e9b988fc34b <adee03f8903c58a6a559f21388a430211fac8ce9"}, {"id": "199f8134-5f57-30ae-ba36-de85d17e98c5", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.11.10"}, {"id": "3884bcf9-0d84-3fe9-bd53-e18d1ae47329", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.12"}, {"id": "7ffb8b43-ffc4-3f75-b97f-4434bd78c9b9", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "9323982a-8b86-3e64-8e4c-15aff1abac76", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.7"}, {"id": "94c1d80f-9ff3-3ba0-91e1-75d2575f8eb4", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "52526ca7fdb905a768a93f8faa418e9b988fc34b <669b0cb81e4e4e78cff77a5b367c7f70c0c6c05e"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "14a47aa2-1e09-3ec4-8806-c6b72df44c35", "vendor": {"name": "Linux"}}], "isExploited": false}